╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 2.3: Collapse and Flip                ║
║  Category: Selection             Difficulty: ★☆☆ Fundamental    ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  ;       Collapse selection to a single cursor
  Alt-;   Flip selection (swap anchor and cursor)

In Helix, every cursor is a selection with an anchor and a head.
  ;  collapses the selection to just the cursor position.
  Alt-;  swaps which end is the anchor and which is the head.

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  This exercise practices the "select then refine" workflow.

  Each line has two words in CAPS. Delete ONLY the second one.

  Strategy:
  1. Use / to search for a CAPS word (or navigate manually)
  2. If you accidentally select too much, use ; to collapse
     and try again
  3. Select precisely the second CAPS word, then d

  This teaches you to use ; as a "reset" when your selection
  goes wrong — a crucial habit in Helix.

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

The QUICK brown LAZY fox.
A TALL tree and SHORT grass.
The FIRST step and LAST dance.
One GOOD deed and BAD habit.

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

The QUICK brown  fox.
A TALL tree and  grass.
The FIRST step and  dance.
One GOOD deed and  habit.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: On the first line, navigate to LAZY. Press w to select
          the word, then d to delete it.
  Hint 2: If you overshoot and select too much, press ; to
          collapse back to a cursor and start over.
  Hint 3: The key habit: ; is your "undo selection" — use it
          freely whenever you need to restart a selection.
